1.get_variation.txt
This text is a simple pipeline to get variation from raw seqence data.

2.get_common_variation.pl
This script was used to get the common variation in two or more M2 populations.

Usage:
	perl 2.get_common_variation.pl -i <vcf> -o <genome.fai> [options]
	--input  -i	The input file of VCF type, including the variation in two or more M2 populations.
	--output -o	The out file of VCF type, including the common variation.
	--conf   -c	The two samples on the row represent the mutant bulk and wild type bulk from a same M2 population.
Exmple:
	perl 2.get_common_variation.pl --input ./Example/input.vcf.gz --output ./Example/common_variation.vcf.gz
	perl 2.get_common_variation.pl --input ./Example/input.vcf.gz --output ./Example/common_variation.vcf.gz --conf ./Example/sample.conf

3.DMAP_M2.pl
Using the filtered SNP variation, this script can calculate the index value and the absolute index value on tandem slide windows to identify the candidate region.

Usage:
	perl 3.DMAP_M2.pl  -f <vcf> -i <genome.fai> [options]
	--vcf	 -f	VCF files
	--index  -i	Genome index generated by samtools
	--win	 -w	Slide window, default 1000000
	--step	 -s	Step length, default 500000
	--common -c The VCF type file including the common variation
	--help	 -h	Help
Example:
	perl 3.DMAP_M2.pl --vcf ./Example/SNP.vcf --index ./Example/gmx.fa.fai --win 1000000 --step 500000 --out ./Example/out
	perl 3.DMAP_M2.pl --vcf ./Example/SNP.vcf --index ./Example/gmx.fa.fai --win 1000000 --step 500000 --out ./Example/out --common ./Example/common_variation.vcf.gz
Noteï¼š
	"SNP.vcf" contains the filtered SNP variation from two bulk of a M2 population.
	"gmx.fa.fai" was the index file generated from the samtools software.
